oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Mansion overlooking Tennessee River
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Mansion belonging to E. Cherry, which overlooks the Tennessee River. There is a stone fence in front of the mansion.
It overlooked the Tennessee River and was the house that U.S. Grant stayed in during the Battle of Shiloh.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Mansions; Masonry
